  "commentary": "With SPX at 6816.97 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6810 (-62.3B) and max positive gamma at 6830 (+24.2B), dealers are currently buying this move as they're caught short gamma in a breakout regime. The massive negative GEX wall cluster from 6800-6815 creates a highly amplifying zone that SPX just broke above, suggesting dealers will continue buying any dips back toward these levels while selling strength into the 6830 positive gamma cap. Watch for continued trending behavior with 6830 acting as initial resistance where dealer selling pressure kicks in, but any break above likely accelerates the move higher given the breakout regime dynamics.\n\nBottom line: expect continued upward momentum with 6830 as the key resistance level to break.",
